Java I/O (Input and Output) is used to process the input and produce the output. 
Java uses the concept of a stream to make I/O operation fast.
File class is used to open a file.
FileInputStream is used to read data from file.
FileOuputStream is used to write data to file.
We have Buffered Reader which reduces the no of disk operations, by storing data in buffer then followed by writing to disk or reading from disk.